WEBVTT

00:02.004 --> 00:03.698
Okay, Zuckerman,

00:03.739 --> 00:05.467
how'd you know
l was into Bukowski, huh?

00:05.508 --> 00:06.531
Come on.

00:06.576 --> 00:08.064
The renegade poet of our times?

00:08.109 --> 00:09.076
Please.

00:09.111 --> 00:10.475
''There's a bluebird in my heart

00:10.513 --> 00:11.877
''that wants to get out,

00:11.914 --> 00:15.815
''but l pour whisky on him
and inhale cigarette smoke.

00:15.850 --> 00:18.943
''All the whores and bartenders
and the grocery clerks

00:18.987 --> 00:22.149
never know that he's in there.''

00:22.224 --> 00:24.748
You think his friends ever tried
to put him in a rehab?

00:24.793 --> 00:27.158
Well, if they didn't,
maybe they should have.

00:27.261 --> 00:28.659
l don't know.

00:28.696 --> 00:31.129
Do you really think that he
could write that kind of stuff

00:31.165 --> 00:32.756
if he got rid
of all his demons?

00:32.800 --> 00:34.164
Who knows?

00:34.201 --> 00:35.827
William Blake.

00:35.869 --> 00:37.836
Blake says,

00:37.871 --> 00:39.599
''The road to excess leads

00:39.639 --> 00:41.503
right to the gates
of the palace of wisdom.''

00:42.542 --> 00:44.031
Excuse me.

00:51.184 --> 00:52.741
Hi. Uh, Mr. McKay?

00:52.784 --> 00:54.011
Yeah.

00:54.052 --> 00:55.916
l've got some registered
mail here for you.

00:55.954 --> 00:58.888
l'll need you to sign
here, please.

01:01.526 --> 01:02.617
-Thanks.
-You're welcome.

01:02.661 --> 01:03.854
Thank you.

01:10.868 --> 01:11.891
What is it?

01:11.936 --> 01:15.837
lt's from Municipal Court.

01:15.873 --> 01:17.897
lt's a notice to appear.

01:17.942 --> 01:19.340
lt's about my accident.

01:19.376 --> 01:20.933
Your accident?

01:20.977 --> 01:24.776
Yeah, l'm being charged:
driving under the influence.

01:24.814 --> 01:26.440
Took 'em long enough.

01:26.483 --> 01:28.677
Yeah, l was beginning to think
it might never come.

01:28.718 --> 01:31.413
Pretty stupid, huh?

01:31.453 --> 01:33.818
Time to face the music.

